# Code Structure Standards

## Folder Structure
lib/
  constants/
    navigation.ts
  utils/
    scroll.ts
  i18n/
    config.ts
    locales/
      en/
        common.json
        hero.json
        navbar.json
        footer.json
hooks/
  useTranslation.ts
  useScrollSection.ts
components/
  ui/          ← already exists from shadcn
  sections/
    Hero.tsx   ← move from components/Hero.tsx
  layout/
    Navbar.tsx ← move from components/Navbar.tsx
    Footer.tsx ← move from components/Footer.tsx

## Import Rules
- Always use @/ alias — never relative paths like ../../
- Constants: import from '@/lib/constants/navigation'
- Utils: import from '@/lib/utils/scroll'
- Hooks: import from '@/hooks/useTranslation'
- UI components: import from '@/components/ui/button'
- Never import between sections/ components directly

## Naming Conventions
- Components: PascalCase (Hero.tsx, Navbar.tsx)
- Hooks: camelCase with use prefix (useTranslation.ts)
- Utils: camelCase (scroll.ts)
- Constants: SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE for values (NAV_ITEMS)
- JSON locale files: snake_case keys

## Component Rules
- Every exported component has a JSDoc comment above it
- Every exported function has a JSDoc comment
- "use client" only when using hooks or browser APIs
- No hardcoded strings in components — use useTranslation
- No hardcoded colors — use CSS variables
- No inline styles except for dynamic values

## CSS Token Rules
- Our custom tokens: --bg-primary, --bg-secondary, --bg-card,
  --text-primary, --text-secondary, --text-muted,
  --custom-border, --lime
- shadcn tokens: --background, --foreground, --primary etc
- Never use --border (shadcn owns this)
- Never use --accent (shadcn owns this)
- Use --custom-border for all border colors
- Use --lime (#CCFF00) for accent/highlight color